text: Birmingham Central Library was the main public library in Birmingham, England. It closed on 29 June 2013 and was replaced with the Library of Birmingham. It was once the largest non-national library in Europe. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:Libraries in the United Kingdom Category:Buildings and structures in Birmingham Category:1974 establishments in England Category:2013 disestablishments in the United Kingdom Category:21st-century disestablishments in England
